00:00:06.650 --> 00:00:08.300
SHEREE HAGGAN: OK,
"The View UpStairs"

00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:10.580
is a provocative new
musical that pulls you

00:00:10.580 --> 00:00:14.490
inside the UpStairs Lounge,
a vibrant '70s gay bar

00:00:14.490 --> 00:00:16.360
in the French Quarter
of New Orleans.

00:00:16.360 --> 00:00:18.310
This forgotten
community comes to life

00:00:18.310 --> 00:00:21.050
when a young fashion
designer from 2017

00:00:21.050 --> 00:00:23.630
buys the abandoned space,
setting off an exhilarating

00:00:23.630 --> 00:00:26.210
journey of seduction
and self exploration

00:00:26.210 --> 00:00:29.060
that "Entertainment Weekly"
calls "a moving homage

00:00:29.060 --> 00:00:31.976
to LGBT culture,
past and present."

00:00:31.976 --> 00:00:33.350
Filled with
"beautiful love songs

00:00:33.350 --> 00:00:35.900
performed by a soulful
ensemble cast."

00:00:35.900 --> 00:00:38.900
So, please help me welcome to
the stage, to perform for us

00:00:38.900 --> 00:00:40.810
now, the cast from
"The View UpStairs."

