this is the person that

00:17:37.990 --> 00:17:39.370
is cast as the role.

00:17:39.370 --> 00:17:40.557
So create chemistry, and go.

00:17:40.557 --> 00:17:41.390
And so we did, and--

00:17:41.390 --> 00:17:41.890
[LAUGHTER]

00:17:41.890 --> 00:17:44.306
TAYLOR FREY: So, usually you
know those things in advance.

00:17:44.306 --> 00:17:44.910
You can prep.

00:17:44.910 --> 00:17:46.380
And they didn't tell
any of the boys.

00:17:46.380 --> 00:17:48.421
JEREMY POPE: They didn't
tell me, which is great.

00:17:48.421 --> 00:17:50.892
But we kissed in the room,
and the sparks were flying.

00:17:50.892 --> 00:17:51.850
TAYLOR FREY: Fireworks.

00:17:51.850 --> 00:17:52.850
JEREMY POPE: Yeah.

00:17:52.850 --> 00:17:55.110
And then, it was a yes, so
feeling great about that.

00:17:55.110 --> 00:17:55.957
[LAUGHTER]

00:17:55.957 --> 00:17:57.290
SHEREE HAGGAN: That's wonderful.

00:17:57.290 --> 00:17:59.200
NANCY TICOTIN: My
story's a little similar

00:17:59.200 --> 00:18:01.660
to Randy's, in that
there was someone

00:18:01.660 --> 00:18:03.630
else in this role prior.

00:18:03.630 --> 00:18:06.950
And she got bumped
up into another job.

00:18:06.950 --> 00:18:08.450
And then, they called me.

00:18:08.450 --> 00:18:10.810
And I was thrown into this.

00:18:10.810 --> 00:18:12.560
I was living upstate
New York in the snow.

00:18:12.560 --> 00:18:14.350
And then, I read the script.

00:18:14.350 --> 00:18:15.350
The next day I said yes.

00:18:15.350 --> 00:18:16.230
I packed two bags.

00:18:16.230 --> 00:18:17.750
The next day, I was
at rehearsal at 10:00

00:18:17.750 --> 00:18:19.125
and didn't know
where I was going

00:18:19.125 --> 00:18:21.620
to be that night-- sleeping
on couches for a long time.

00:18:21.620 --> 00:18:23.150
But out of the blue,
just like that.

00:18:23.150 --> 00:18:24.933
I didn't know that about
Randy, interesting.

00:18:24.933 --> 00:18:25.724
SHEREE HAGGAN: Wow.

00:18:25.724 --> 00:18:26.727
That's beautiful.

00:18:26.727 --> 00:18:29.720
Now, you had mentioned, Nathan,
that this is a true story.

00:18:29.720 --> 00:18:30.140
NATHAN LEE GRAHAM: Yeah.

00:18:30.140 --> 00:18:30.770
SHEREE HAGGAN: And
can you tell me more?

00:18:30.770 --> 00:18:32.450
NATHAN LEE GRAHAM: Well,
it's based upon a true story.

00:18:32.450 --> 00:18:32.770
SHEREE HAGGAN: Yeah.

00:18:32.770 --> 00:18:33.811
NATHAN LEE GRAHAM: Well--

00:18:33.811 --> 00:18:38.300
and anyone can please jump in
and modify or correct, please--

00:18:38.300 --> 00:18:40.670
but in 1973, there
was an arson attack

00:18:40.670 --> 00:18:45.290
at a lounge called the
UpStairs Lounge in New Orleans.

00:18:45.290 --> 00:18:49.550
And they're not sure
who started the fire.

00:18:49.550 --> 00:18:53.330
But this fire did
indeed killed 32 people.

00:18:53.330 --> 00:18:55.190
Some people got out.

00:18:55.190 --> 00:18:56.910
But it is 1973.

00:18:56.910 --> 00:18:57.740
This is the south.

00:18:57.740 --> 00:18:58.550
It is New Orleans.

00:18:58.550 --> 00:19:02.450
And so, it was under-reported,
under-investigated,

00:19:02.450 --> 00:19:06.980
and to this day,
you can literally--

00:19:06.980 --> 00:19:10.160
all joking aside-- Google it
and find out more about it.

00:19:10.160 --> 00:19:12.230
But it's still an
under-reported,

00:19:12.230 --> 00:19:14.030
under-investigated story.

00:19:14.030 --> 00:19:16.950
And it's our first
Orlando, if you will,

00:19:16.950 --> 00:19:18.980
for the LGBTQ community.

00:19:18.980 --> 00:19:22.280
So it's an important
story, a pivotal story.

00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:27.290
And what Max has done is taken
the wonderful character of Wes,

00:19:27.290 --> 00:19:30.830
that Jeremy plays,
from the present day

00:19:30.830 --> 00:19:33.980
and transports him back to 1973.

00:19:33.980 --> 00:19:36.290
And we all come alive.

00:19:36.290 --> 00:19:40.700
And all of the machinations,
and contradictions,

00:19:40.700 --> 00:19:45.140
and differences between
1973 and the present day all

00:19:45.140 --> 00:19:51.410
happen in this one bar
before this tragedy happens.

00:19:51.410 --> 00:19:53.630
And so, it's a beautiful
story about something

00:19:53.630 --> 00:19:56.272
that was tragic that
needs to be told.

00:19:56.272 --> 00:19:57.980
And I'm just so proud
to be a part of it.

00:19:57.980 --> 00:19:59.041
Does anyone want to add?

00:19:59.041 --> 00:20:01.040
RANDY REDD: Yeah, as far
as under-reported goes,

00:20:01.040 --> 00:20:03.050
I grew up just north
of New Orleans.

00:20:03.050 --> 00:20:06.440
I was probably 10, 11, 12
years old when this happened.

00:20:06.440 --> 00:20:07.980
And never knew of it.

00:20:07.980 --> 00:20:11.576
Never heard about it
until this show came up.

00:20:11.576 --> 00:20:13.700
And there's still-- I talk
to my friends and family

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:16.250
back home, and even
people in New Orleans who

00:20:16.250 --> 00:20:17.644
don't know this story.

00:20:17.644 --> 00:20:19.310
And it's just outrageous
to me that it's

00:20:19.310 --> 00:20:24.657
gone so missing from our
history, certainly, you know.

00:20:24.657 --> 00:20:25.740
SHEREE HAGGAN: Absolutely.

00:20:25.740 --> 00:20:28.100
TAYLOR FREY: What's cool is that
now people are seeing the show.

00:20:28.100 --> 00:20:29.930
And I have two people
that have contacted

00:20:29.930 --> 00:20:33.350
me who have had trips planned
to New Orleans already,

00:20:33.350 --> 00:20:35.480
saw the show, and went
and found the bar,

00:20:35.480 --> 00:20:37.272
and looked and saw the
names outside of it.

00:20:37.272 --> 00:20:38.480
There's some in the sidewalk.

00:20:38.480 --> 00:20:39.780
There's some on the building.

00:20:39.780 --> 00:20:41.550
And so, that's really special.

00:20:41.550 --> 00:20:43.850
We get to kind of
honor those lives now.

00:20:43.850 --> 00:20:45.666
It's really something rare.

00:20:45.666 --> 00:20:47.124
NATHAN LEE GRAHAM:
It's incredible.

00:20:47.124 --> 00:20:48.795
SHEREE HAGGAN: Now,
it was under-reported.

00:20:48.795 --> 00:20:50.140
And you guys mention
that quite a bit

00:20:50.140 --> 00:20:51.410
that the news didn't cover it.

00:20:51.410 --> 00:20:54.130
Why do you feel like
it wasn't covered

00:20:54.130 --> 00:20:55.580
when so many lives were lost?

00:20:55.580 --> 00:20:57.560
Before Orlando, which
you had mentioned,

00:20:57.560 --> 00:21:01.811
this was the largest attack
on the LGBT community.

00:21:01.811 --> 00:21:03.560
NATHAN LEE GRAHAM:
Does anybody want to--?

00:21:03.560 --> 00:21:05.143
ANTHONY ALFARO: Well,
I would probably

00:21:05.143 --> 00:21:08.670
say that it was because
they were all gay.

00:21:08.670 --> 00:21:11.510
And I think that, not only
was it under-reported,

00:21:11.510 --> 00:21:16.050
but the families
of the victims--

00:21:16.050 --> 00:21:18.350
I'm sure a lot of them
were quite embarrassed

00:21:18.350 --> 00:21:22.520
or felt some sort of shame
about having their kids,

00:21:22.520 --> 00:21:26.435
or their kin, or relatives at
this place that was kind of--

00:21:26.435 --> 00:21:28.560
NATHAN LEE GRAHAM: Well,
I mean you would be fired.

00:21:28.560 --> 00:21:28.885
ANTHONY ALFARO: Yeah.

00:21:28.885 --> 00:21:29.210
NATHAN LEE GRAHAM: Yes.

