so scared about it.

00:40:54.870 --> 00:40:58.650
But with this show,
I mean she struggled.

00:40:58.650 --> 00:41:00.010
It wasn't like, oh, you're gay.

00:41:00.010 --> 00:41:00.670
It's fine.

00:41:00.670 --> 00:41:02.970
No-- she went through
a lot of hassles.

00:41:02.970 --> 00:41:04.090
And she was scared.

00:41:04.090 --> 00:41:06.120
And she doesn't know
anything about how

00:41:06.120 --> 00:41:09.720
to live a life with
a gay guy, her kids.

00:41:09.720 --> 00:41:11.394
And then the husband leaves her.

00:41:11.394 --> 00:41:12.060
And she's there.

00:41:12.060 --> 00:41:13.620
And she's struggling on her own.

00:41:13.620 --> 00:41:14.467
But that's the love.

00:41:14.467 --> 00:41:15.300
SHEREE HAGGAN: Yeah.

00:41:15.300 --> 00:41:17.340
NANCY TICOTIN: And
it's a mother's love,

00:41:17.340 --> 00:41:20.490
not just for him, but
for everybody in the bar.

00:41:20.490 --> 00:41:22.890
You know, like, I feel like
it's kind of a universal--

00:41:22.890 --> 00:41:26.310
I'm the "big momma," you know.

00:41:26.310 --> 00:41:28.867
And I'm so connected to
Michael, who plays the role.

00:41:28.867 --> 00:41:29.700
SHEREE HAGGAN: Yeah.

00:41:29.700 --> 00:41:31.283
NANCY TICOTIN: We
just have this bond.

00:41:31.283 --> 00:41:33.180
And we have a lot
of fun with it.

00:41:33.180 --> 00:41:35.160
But it's a challenging--

00:41:35.160 --> 00:41:36.559
I find that the whole show--

00:41:36.559 --> 00:41:38.850
and I'm used to doing singing,
and dancing, and acting,

00:41:38.850 --> 00:41:40.230
and kicking my
legs, and all that.

00:41:40.230 --> 00:41:41.604
And I don't do
that in this show.

00:41:41.604 --> 00:41:43.830
But I find the show
very challenging

00:41:43.830 --> 00:41:46.290
mentally, vocally, emotionally.

00:41:46.290 --> 00:41:48.420
It takes a lot of
my concentration.

00:41:48.420 --> 00:41:49.510
And I love that.

00:41:49.510 --> 00:41:52.340
Because then I'm
growing, and I'm sharing.

00:41:52.340 --> 00:41:53.840
I love to have that
challenge, yeah.

00:41:53.840 --> 00:41:54.673
SHEREE HAGGAN: Yeah.

00:41:54.673 --> 00:41:56.557
It sounds like this
character embodies

00:41:56.557 --> 00:41:58.890
some of who you are, too,
like that truth in the moment.

00:41:58.890 --> 00:41:59.973
NANCY TICOTIN: Absolutely.

