last question for you

00:42:26.430 --> 00:42:29.400
guys today, this is for Nathan--

00:42:29.400 --> 00:42:32.770
what would you think is the
biggest difference in terms

00:42:32.770 --> 00:42:38.040
of dating, 1973 to today?

00:42:38.040 --> 00:42:42.140
NATHAN LEE GRAHAM: Well,
all of you kids are spoiled.

00:42:42.140 --> 00:42:44.172
[LAUGHTER]

00:42:45.030 --> 00:42:46.740
Nowadays you can't
walk into a bathroom

00:42:46.740 --> 00:42:49.740
without 10 guys following
you into your stall.

00:42:49.740 --> 00:42:53.190
[LAUGHTER]

00:42:53.190 --> 00:42:56.790
But, once upon a time,
things were not so simple.

00:42:56.790 --> 00:43:01.200
There was no cruising
on the bread lines.

00:43:01.200 --> 00:43:04.750
In my early 20s, I had to
intercept more coded messages

00:43:04.750 --> 00:43:05.820
than the allied forces.

00:43:05.820 --> 00:43:09.140
[LAUGHTER]

00:43:09.140 --> 00:43:11.730
But I was hungry for love.

00:43:11.730 --> 00:43:14.160
And I certainly found it--

00:43:14.160 --> 00:43:19.510
painters, poets,
diplomats, sailors galore.

00:43:19.510 --> 00:43:22.665
[LAUGHTER] Even a
sword swallower.

00:43:22.665 --> 00:43:25.914
[LAUGHTER]

00:43:27.910 --> 00:43:32.050
They, of course, fell
deeply in love with me.

00:43:32.050 --> 00:43:34.390
How could they not?

00:43:34.390 --> 00:43:36.130
It is an undisputed
fact that I had

00:43:36.130 --> 00:43:42.270
the best legs in all of
N'Orleans, for a man or woman.

00:43:42.270 --> 00:43:43.090
[LAUGHTER]

00:43:43.090 --> 00:43:45.340
Mr. Balanchine told
me himself when

00:43:45.340 --> 00:43:49.150
I auditioned for the ballet
"Russe de Monte Carlo"

00:43:49.150 --> 00:43:50.225
in 1940--

00:43:50.225 --> 00:43:51.100
keep your mouth shut.

00:43:51.100 --> 00:43:53.630
[LAUGHTER]

00:43:53.630 --> 00:43:57.100
Now, mind you--
and I'm no dancer--

00:43:57.100 --> 00:43:59.930
but he was ready to
take me on my silhouette

00:43:59.930 --> 00:44:12.260
alone, except for that nasty
prima ballerina, Danilova.

00:44:12.260 --> 00:44:17.450
Oh, she was a fright,
and jealous, too.

00:44:17.450 --> 00:44:19.580
How I would have loved to
tweeze every wayward hair

00:44:19.580 --> 00:44:21.230
of her boorish, Russian face.

00:44:21.230 --> 00:44:22.320
[LAUGHTER]

00:44:22.320 --> 00:44:26.850
But who would have
known where to begin?

00:44:26.850 --> 00:44:30.182
[LAUGHTER]

00:44:32.030 --> 00:44:32.530
That's all.

00:44:32.530 --> 00:44:34.514
